  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and declared; a screening sensitivity study is described in the UQ narrative but no structured hasSensitivityAnalysis link is encoded, leaving dominant input drivers uncharacterized. Full 13-factor assessment covers all required ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Decision: Accepted.",
