      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ validation run — absolute hemolysis index across 5 operating points",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000) was performed across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity distributions. Predicted hemolysis index distributions were compared against available experimental measurements. A screening sensitivity study was conducted during UQ setup to identify potentially influential parameters; results are summarized in the UQ narrative report but are not formally linked as a structured sensitivity analysis artifact. Prediction intervals bracket experimental data at 4 of 5 operating conditions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vad-grid-convergence",
