    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps relative to MRL 5 requirements, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ bounds are conservative and bracket experimental data at 4 of 5 operating points. The UQ narrative describes a screening sensitivity study identifying hemolysis model coefficient C as the dominant driver; this verbal characterization was considered sufficient by the assessment team. The structured sensitivity analysis link was not encoded as a formal artifact, as the team considered the narrative description adequate for the current submission stage. Remaining factor gaps (use error, test samples, equivalency of input parameters) are documented as open items for the next assessment cycle.",
